 dlisregarding information that points to other possible conclusions."},{"type":"text","text":"embody, externalize, incarnate, materialize"},{"type":"text","text":"substantiation (n.证明，证实)"},{"type":"entry","text":"choice","headword":"choice"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.上等的(of high quality);精选的(selected with care)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tors]"},{"type":"text","text":"dainty, delicate, elegant, exquisite, superior"},{"type":"entry","text":"reliance","headword":"reliance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 信赖, 信任(the state of being dependent on or having confidence in)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'larans]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自rely（v依赖）"},{"type":"text","text":"The success of science is due in great part to its emphasis on objectivity: the"},{"type":"text","text":"reliance on evidence rather than preconceptions and the willingness to draw"},{"type":"text","text":"conclusions even when they conflict with traditional beliefs."},{"type":"entry","text":"virtual","headword":"virtual"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 实质上的，实际上的(being such in essence or effect though not formally"},{"type":"text","text":"['v3:rtfual]"},{"type":"text","text":"recognized or admitted)"},{"type":"entry","text":"inspired","headword":"inspired"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj有创见的，有灵感的(outstanding or brilliant in a way or to a degree suggestive"},{"type":"text","text":"[1n'sparard]"},{"type":"text","text":"of divine inspiration)"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：in（使）+spir（呼吸）+ed→吸入（灵气）→有灵感的"},{"type":"text","text":"Her first concert appearance was disappointingly perfunctory and derivative,"},{"type":"example","text":"rather than the inspirec performance in the innovative style we had anticipated."}]},{"number":173,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"elate","headword":"elate"},{"type":"text","text":"使高兴，使得意（to fil with joy or pride)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'lert]"},{"type":"text","text":"commove, exhilarate, intoxicate"},{"type":"text","text":"elated（adj.得意的，振奋的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"sustained","headword":"sustained"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj持久的，持续的（prolonged）"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'steind]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自sustain（v保持）"},{"type":"text","text":"Exposure to suslained noise has been claimed to impair blood pressure"},{"type":"text","text":"regulation in human beings and, particularly, to increase hypertension, even"},{"type":"text","text":"though some researchers have obtained inconclusive results that obscure."},{"type":"entry","text":"panic","headword":"panic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.恐慌的 n.恐慌，惊惶(a sudden unreasoning terror)"},{"type":"text","text":"['paenrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自希腊神话中的畜牧神潘（Pan），panic是指潘的出现所引起的恐惧"},{"type":"text","text":"B During the Battle of Trafalgar, Admiral Nelson remained imperturbable and in"},{"type":"example","text":"full command of the situation in spite of the hysteria and panic all around him."},{"type":"entry","text":"wage","headword":"wage"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.开始，进行(to begin and continue)"},{"type":"text","text":"[we1d3]"},{"type":"text","text":"wageawar进行战争"},{"type":"text","text":"budget"},{"type":"entry","text":"budget","headword":"budget"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 预 (plan of how money will be spent over a period of"},{"type":"text","text":"[bAd31t]"},{"type":"text","text":"time）v.做预算，安排开支（toplan in advance the"},{"type":"text","text":"预算"},{"type":"text","text":"expenditure of)"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：bud（花蕾）+get（得到）→得到花蕾开始卖→做"},{"type":"text","text":"预算"},{"type":"text","text":"on a (tight) budget 拮据"},{"type":"entry","text":"inspiration","headword":"inspiration"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 启示，灵感(thought or emotion inspired by sth.)"},{"type":"text","text":"[inspa'rer{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：in（使）+spir（呼吸）+ation→吸入（灵气）→灵感"},{"type":"entry","text":"forward","headword":"forward"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.过激的（extreme);莽撞的（bold)，冒失的，无礼的"},{"type":"text","text":"[fo:rward]"},{"type":"not